<div id="review_3549981919" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3549981919" />
    <a title="John McDermott" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/24209189-john-mcdermott"><img alt="John McDermott" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1642846928p2/24209189.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3549981919?book_show_action=true">Nov 09, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="John McDermott" class="user" itemprop="url" name="John McDermott" href="/user/show/24209189-john-mcdermott">John McDermott</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781471133701" href="/book/show/20760065-american-rust">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3549981919" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9254300209789051115">American Rust was a bleak but rewarding read that despite being published in 2009 is still depressingly relevant today. Set in a small town in Pennsylvania, which has seen it&apos;s major sources of employment in steel and coal outsourced overseas, it features Isaac and Billy Poe ; two young men with genuine talent who never the less are trapped by their circumstances. When Isaac resolves to leave town ,Billy decides to help only for a horrifying act of violence to alter their future .The effect of t</span>
  <span id="freeText9254300209789051115" style="display:none">American Rust was a bleak but rewarding read that despite being published in 2009 is still depressingly relevant today. Set in a small town in Pennsylvania, which has seen it's major sources of employment in steel and coal outsourced overseas, it features Isaac and Billy Poe ; two young men with genuine talent who never the less are trapped by their circumstances. When Isaac resolves to leave town ,Billy decides to help only for a horrifying act of violence to alter their future .The effect of this act and it's consequences on our protagonists and everyone around then is wonderfully done. It would have been easy to caricature all the characters,who live in a small dying town where people who previously had well paid jobs are now long term unemployed or forced to take unskilled minimum wage jobs. Thankfully, Philipp Meyer avoids this trap and describe his characters honestly and with compassion. Strong writing throughout the book ; I suspect the author would make a great crime writer. Definitely recommended.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9254300209789051115" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


