              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7792414225113585333">I truly enjoyed this gripping tale of murder and conscience which occurs in western Pennsylvania, the eponymous American Rust Belt. I found that the shifting perspective among the various protagonists was well done. The descriptions are vivid and the action is quite intense as well. I was confused why the female protagonist disappears from the last chapter entirely, but felt that the whole tapestry of the lives impacted held together well. I am really looking forward to reading his latest book a</span>
  <span id="freeText7792414225113585333" style="display:none">I truly enjoyed this gripping tale of murder and conscience which occurs in western Pennsylvania, the eponymous American Rust Belt. I found that the shifting perspective among the various protagonists was well done. The descriptions are vivid and the action is quite intense as well. I was confused why the female protagonist disappears from the last chapter entirely, but felt that the whole tapestry of the lives impacted held together well. I am really looking forward to reading his latest book and Pulitzer runnerup, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/16240761.The_Son" title="The Son by Philipp Meyer" rel="nofollow noopener">The Son</a>.</span>
