<div id="review_4248674893" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4248674893" />
    <a title="Dan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10770371-dan"><img alt="Dan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1540580928p2/10770371.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4248674893?book_show_action=true">Dec 25, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dan" href="/user/show/10770371-dan">Dan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4248674893" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14303257454338150078">I did like the story. The themes of American Rust and hopelessness ooze through the book. The imagery is powerful - particularly those of the murder early in the book and the subsequent scenes of Isaac wandering through the woods. <br/><br/>I am not a huge fan of stream of consciousness writing. As a result the sentence structure here is a bit choppy but the messaging and style are consistent and deliberate - so tolerable. <br/><br/>The story reminds me of The Road by Cormac McCarthy - only much more realistic and </span>
  <span id="freeText14303257454338150078" style="display:none">I did like the story. The themes of American Rust and hopelessness ooze through the book. The imagery is powerful - particularly those of the murder early in the book and the subsequent scenes of Isaac wandering through the woods. <br /><br />I am not a huge fan of stream of consciousness writing. As a result the sentence structure here is a bit choppy but the messaging and style are consistent and deliberate - so tolerable. <br /><br />The story reminds me of The Road by Cormac McCarthy - only much more realistic and less apocalyptic. <br /><br />4 stars.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14303257454338150078" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


